						</tr>
					</table>
					<p></p>
					<p><span style="color:green;"><b>Binary to decimal conversion</b></span></p>
					<p>For binary number with n digits:</p>
					<p>d<sub>n-1</sub>... d<sub>3&nbsp</sub>d<sub>2&nbsp</sub>d<sub>1&nbsp</sub>d<sub>0&nbsp</sub></p>
					<p>The decimal number is equal to the sum of binary digits (dn) times their power of 2 (2<sup>n</sup>):</p>
					<p>decimal = d<sub>0</sub>x2<sup>0</sup> + d<sub>1</sub>x2<sup>1</sup> + d<sub>2</sub>x2<sup>2</sup> + ...</p>
					<p><b>Example</b></p>
					<table class="table2" style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
						<tr>
							<td class="table2 tableheader" style="text-align:left;padding-top:5px; padding-bottom:5px;"><b>binary number:&nbsp&nbsp</b></td >
							<td class="table2">1</td >
							<td class="table2">0</td >
							<td class="table2">0</td >
							<td class="table2">1</td >
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="table2 tableheader" style="text-align:left; padding-top:5px; padding-bottom:5px;"><b>power of 2:&nbsp&nbsp</b></td >
							<td class="table2">2<sup>3</sup></td >
							<td class="table2">2<sup>2</sup></td >
							<td class="table2">2<sup>1</sup></td >
							<td class="table2">2<sup>0</sup></td >
						</tr>
					</table>
					<p></p>
					<p><span style="color:green;"><b>Decimal to binary conversion</b></span></p>
					<p>Conversion steps:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Divide the number by 2.</li>
						<li>Get the integer quotient for the next iteration.</li>
						<li>Get the remainder for the binary digit.</li>
						<li>Repeat the steps until the quotient is equal to 0.</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Convert 13 to binary:</p>
					<table style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto; ">
						<tr>
							<td class="td3 tableheader"><b>Division by 2</b></td >
							<td class="td3 tableheader"><b>Quotient</b></td >
							<td class="td3 tableheader"><b>Remainder</b></td >
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="td3">13/2</td>
							<td class="td3">6</td>
							<td class="td3" style="background-color:#FFF5EE">1</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="td3">6/2</td>
							<td class="td3">3</td>
							<td class="td3" style="background-color:#FFF5EE">0</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="td3">3/2</td>
							<td class="td3">1</td>
							<td class="td3" style="background-color:#FFF5EE">1</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="td3">1/2</td>
							<td class="td3">0</td>
							<td class="td3" style="background-color:#FFF5EE">1</td>
						</tr>
					</table>
					<p></p>
					<p>So 13 as a decimal numebrs equals 1101 as a binary number.</p>
